'{"corrected_text":"CENTRAL CRIMINAL COURT. (Before Mr. Justice Stephen.) Mr McKean, K.C., Senior Crown Prose¬ cutor NOT GUILTY. ON GROUND OF INSANITY. Kathleen May Beeby, 30, was charged with having murdered her son Jack Beeby, aged 5 years, at Wollongong, on May 9 last. Mr McKean said that the unfortunate woman, who was single, was found on Wol¬ longong beach after she had walked into the sea. The child, who was strapped to her, was dead. The accused had been in domestic service and was in desperate circumstances. Her child was subnormal, and it would be sub¬ mitted that at the time the tragedy occurred accused was temporarily insane. Accused had made a statement to the effect that she in¬ tended to drown herself and the boy. It was stated in evidence that, accused had done war work and had emigrated to Aus¬ tralia. Dr Holloway, visiting surgeon at Long Bay Penitentiary, said he had examined accused on several occasions since May 12. In his opinion she was normal. "Certainly she is not insane," he added. Nellie McKenzie Gray, matron of a home for the destitute and betrayed, stated that she had known accused since 1926, when she was an inmate of the home. Accused was passionately fond of her son and was a \\"won¬ derful mother.\\" The jury returned a verdict of not guilty on the ground of insanity. His Honor directed that accused be kept in custody during the Governor\'s pleasure. Mr Brian Clancy and Mr W. F. Sheahan (instructed by Messrs Owen and Son, of Wol¬ longong, by their Sydney agents, Messrs A. J. Taylor, William Arnott, and Co.) appeared for the accused. TRIAL POSTPONED. On the application of Mr Sheahan his Honor postponed until the next sittings of the Court the trial of Alfred John Dillon, 21, who, it was stated, is to be charged with hav¬ ing murdered Cecil William Bethel McCor¬ mack in William-street, city, on May 13 last. Dillon stood his trial on this charge at the present sittings early this month, but the jury disagreed, and Dillon was remanded for trial. Mr Sheahan (Instructed by Messrs.","has_modifications":true}'
